**Code Explanation:**

This script loads all saved results from Steps 1 and 2 and generates four publication-quality plots: 1. Plot 1 (Learning Curves): Loads per-seed training logs (log_A/B_*.csv), interpolates episode returns onto a common step grid, computes mean +/- std across 5 seeds, applies a rolling window smoother, and draws a horizontal reference line at 90% of the maximum mean reward. 2. Plot 2 (Critic Loss): Same approach for critic loss - interpolates onto a common step grid, computes mean +/- std, and plots with shaded confidence bands. 3. Plot 3 (Value Function Heatmaps): Loads the precomputed grid arrays (phi_grid, q_grid_A, q_grid_B, f_grid_B) and theta/thetadot axes, then renders a 2x2 subplot grid with consistent colorbars. The first three panels share a color scale; the residual panel uses its own scale. 4. Plot 4 (Summary Metrics): Loads eval_results.csv and sample_efficiency.csv, computes mean +/- std across seeds for upright fraction and sample efficiency steps, and renders side-by-side bar charts with error bars.

